{Partner opened and you hold a monster — a solid spade suit and twenty-three points — so you show the power in one bid and let the partnership drive toward slam with room to spare.
[BID 1C] Partner opens 1\C, promising at least three clubs and an opening hand.
[BID 2S] You jump-shift to 2\S, a Soloway jump — game-forcing with slam interest, showing a self-sufficient spade suit and six controls: two aces and two kings, past the four the bid guarantees.
[BID 3C] Partner rebids 3\C, showing a genuine second suit rather than a fit for your spades.
[BID 3S] You rebid 3\S to stamp your suit as solid, good enough to be trumps opposite a singleton, so partner can commit to spades.
[BID 4N] Partner takes over with Roman Keycard Blackwood, asking how many of the four aces and the spade king you hold.
